Hope y’all are doing well!  My life has been crazy. Back on September 30, my sister made the decision to stop doing curative treatment for her metastatic breast cancer, moved in with me and is in hospice. This has been one of the hardest things I’ve ever had to do, but I know I need to be there for her. If you feel like sending up prayers for peace and comfort, we would be so appreciative!

I hope y’all have a fun and safe night!

Well I’ve been dreading this post and putting it off for a few weeks now. As some of you may know my sister was in the fight of her life against metastatic breast cancer.  She had breast cancer in 2005 and chose to have a double mastectomy and went through chemo. She went almost 15 years cancer free. Then, in 2019, the same type of breast cancer came back but in her bones.  She went through several chemo pills then IV chemo and much more.  In early/mid September her lab numbers were so far down they couldn’t give her chemo and she decided to stop treatment. She came to live with me and be on home hospice.  This did give us time together one on one and there were several late nights where we had great talks.  On 11/20 at 7:25 pm she passed away with me holding one hand and her son holding the other hand. She was 59 years old. In that moment when she stopped breathing, a large piece of my heart was taken and left a huge hole that can never be filled. My life will be forever changed!  After 55 years with your best friend who was there for you and you for her, no matter what, what do I do now.  My heart is totally broken 💔😢💔. I know she has gone to a better place and is now pain free, but my heart needs help understanding it.  Her memorial service was our final “see you soon”. I have shared a few pics in this post, and I want to figure out the best way to play her photo tribute. We were total opposites but also 
the same ❤️. The last 14 months have been the hardest ever with losing my dad and then my sister.  Praying for peace and comfort as I try to figure out my life without her. 🙏❤️

#sisterlove❤️ #cancersucks #fcancer #mybestfriend❤️
